Body supine, hands placed above the pelvis, head pointing NW.

Rect. shaft. Brick lined down to hard gebel. Chs. to N & to S. Plundered.
In shaft: Wooden hand fr. coffin, 4 bl. gl. fly amulets, Small discoid bl. gl. beads, Small bone disc.
In N chamber: poor bl. gl. scarab, Alab. kohl pot (no necl), Rough flint, Bone disc (as in shaft), Piece of flat alab. vase, Half of haematite kohl stick, 2 wooden kohl sticks, Wooden comb (poor condition), Copper callipers, Wooden Shabti similar to sev. found near a damaged burial near the shaft.
